Yes. I thought I understood the task until the end but the last question I found very confusing.
Also, it seemed to me a previous question that I marked inconsistent but was graded consistent  I still think was in error. The question stated: 
Dr. Tenni is a professor.
Dr. Ferous is a professor.
Pottery is a class.
Sculpture #1 is an assignment.
Dr. Tenni is the instructor of Pottery.
Dr. Ferous is an assistant for Pottery.
Dr. Tenni is enrolled in Pottery.
Sculpture #1 is associated with Pottery.

The grading policy involves persons, classes and assignments.
A person is either a student (has no title) or a professor (has a Dr. title).
Exactly one professor is the instructor of each class.
At least one person is the assistant for each class.
At least one person is enrolled in each class.
Each assignment is associated with exactly one class.
For each class, only students can be assistants.
How is this consistent? Only students can be assistants. Dr. Ferous isn't a student.

Dr. Tenni is a professor.
Dr. Ferous is a professor.
Pottery is a class.
Sculpture #1 is an assignment.
Dr. Tenni is the instructor of Pottery.
Dr. Ferous is an assistant for Pottery.
Dr. Tenni is enrolled in Pottery.
Sculpture #1 is associated with Pottery.

The grading policy involves persons, classes and assignments.
A person is either a student (has no title) or a professor (has a Dr. title).
Exactly one professor is the instructor of each class.
At least one person is the assistant for each class.
At least one person is enrolled in each class.
Each assignment is associated with exactly one class.
For each class, only students can be assistants.
How is this consistent? Only students can be assistants. Dr. Ferous isn't a student.

Dr. Tenni is a professor.
Dr. Ferous is a professor.
Pottery is a class.
Sculpture #1 is an assignment.
Dr. Tenni is the instructor of Pottery.
Dr. Ferous is an assistant for Pottery.
Dr. Tenni is enrolled in Pottery.
Sculpture #1 is associated with Pottery.

The grading policy involves persons, classes and assignments.
A person is either a student (has no title) or a professor (has a Dr. title).
Exactly one professor is the instructor of each class.
At least one person is the assistant for each class.
At least one person is enrolled in each class.
Each assignment is associated with exactly one class.
For each class, only students can be assistants.
How is this consistent? Only students can be assistants. Dr. Ferous isn't a student.

Dr. Tenni is a professor.
Dr. Ferous is a professor.
Pottery is a class.
Sculpture #1 is an assignment.
Dr. Tenni is the instructor of Pottery.
Dr. Ferous is an assistant for Pottery.
Dr. Tenni is enrolled in Pottery.
Sculpture #1 is associated with Pottery.

The grading policy involves persons, classes and assignments.
A person is either a student (has no title) or a professor (has a Dr. title).
Exactly one professor is the instructor of each class.
At least one person is the assistant for each class.
At least one person is enrolled in each class.
Each assignment is associated with exactly one class.
For each class, only students can be assistants.
How is this consistent? Only students can be assistants. Dr. Ferous isn't a student.
